<Issue id="30389" key="FABCT-44" number="44" project="10609" reporter="mrkiouak" assignee="mrkiouak" creator="mrkiouak" type="10001" summary="Add multi-file support to chaintool proto cmd" priority="4" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2018-05-18 14:12:35.0" updated="2018-07-20 19:17:31.0" resolutiondate="2018-05-19 14:10:30.0" votes="0" watches="1" timeoriginalestimate="3600" timeestimate="3600" workflowId="32796"> <description><! CDATA Currently, fabric chaintool expects a single filename passed to the proto subcommand, and rejects multiple files.  When creating client applications, it is convenient to convert and export the .cci files to .proto format for use in the client application.  chaintool proto should be improved to support this activity with the run of a single command e.g. {code:java} chaintool proto --output ~/active-projects/fabric-client/protos ./*.cci {code}  ></description> </Issue>
